Holidays are not everywhere free
In Hungary, holidays are strictly regulated by law and it has already become a common practice that working days are moved around the holidays, which is expected less often next year.
In the European Union and in the United States, holidays are not uniform.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and state holidays and working days of rest.
The days of work rest are usually devoted to church holidays or to important historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year: the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year is free of work - on New Year's Day already so that people can relax after New Year's Eve.
During the year we have a total of eleven free holidays.
The national holiday is the 15th of March, celebrating the Revolution of 1848 and the 23rd of October, commemorative day of the Revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1, work, on November 1 and 2, we remember the deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, we have two-day holidays Easter, Summer and Christmas.
Since our national, national, or religious holidays rarely fall on the weekend according to the calendar, it has become the practice to move the working day in cases where we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
The price for extended weekends, of course, is that we stay in the workplace and at school on the previous Saturdays.
When we work out the day immediately preceding or following the holiday, the Minister of Labor has been making a special decree for many years.
The legislation applies equally to all employers and their employees, to public employees as well as to persons in the public service.
It does not, however, apply to companies and institutions which are in operation without interruption or which, with regard to their intended purpose, also operate on working days of rest.
This year there will be a change in the working order only around the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24, life in the country will almost stop, because according to previous experience, most people work days between Christmas and New Year's Eve in advance or thus take advantage of a saved holiday.
Next year, several of our holidays fall in the middle, or at the end of the week, respectively, so that the shifts of the working day will be less than this year.
For the first time, the calendar changes around Labor Day so that workers can then stay at home for four days of taste.
Saturday 26 April will be a working day, so that Friday 2 May can be a day of rest.
Another shift is related to the holiday of October 23: on Saturday, October 18, the place will be working on Friday, October 24.
However, the end of the year next year will be able to take place entirely in celebration of the holidays, because from December 24 they will have almost everywhere non-stop holidays even though New Year's Eve falls on Wednesday.
