Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of the driver's license, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insurer.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive an agreed amount of insurance for taking care of the payment of damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of the driver's license, type of vehicle being insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely it is that a crash will occur, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower insurance premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies concluded that people living in marriage have fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of travel, and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
The increase in the frequency of travel increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the price of an insurance policy.
Therefore, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the type of insurance that best suits his insurer profile.
We will show here the most important variables for the selection of this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of insurer, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face various disadvantages such as little driving experience and a short driving license when they want to arrange insurance at an affordable price.
Although insurance is ideal for good coverage against all risks, there are cheaper options as well.
The most observant drivers can choose insurance against all risks with the insurance company discount so that they get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would involve the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"The part of the insurance event payment provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the insurance premium, which will be the higher, the lower the participation," explains Luis Noguera, chief executive of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants of the operation so that the client insures against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your insurance in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the base rate that the insurance company has.
On the contrary, the malus is an increase in the said basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," Noguera explains.
After crossing the twenty-five-year limit, it is easier for drivers when they go to arrange insurance, as the client’s risk index is reduced for them, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks with a discount.
"Young people usually cannot take advantage of the experience gained in advance at the time of the accident, and even when driving," says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of the procedure, when the "fear of the novice" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which could amount to 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other participants of the operation, starting in the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their management is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount,” Luis Noguera notes.
Pensioners are advised to take out insurance against all risks with a discount of insurance (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other participants of the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It has to be said that car insurance is important not only because it protects the driver in the event of a crash, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to study the insurance options that would suit us most in view of our personal situation.
